2. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper uses visual perception to solve the problem of block stacking, which is a key component of computer vision. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an end-to-end learning-based approach and a deep reinforcement learning framework to solve the problem of block stacking, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes machine learning-based solutions to predict stability and learn physics constraints for block stacking. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the problem of controlling a robotic system to stack blocks while satisfying physics constraints, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
